      {
          title: "The Science Behind Addiction",
          slug: "science-of-addiction",
          category: "Education",
          excerpt: "Understanding the neurological and psychological mechanisms that drive addiction can help dispel myths.",
          image: "https://source.unsplash.com/random/300x200/?brain,science"
      },
      {
          title: "How to Talk to Teens About Drugs",
          slug: "talking-to-teens",
          category: "Prevention",
          excerpt: "Effective communication strategies for parents to discuss substance abuse with adolescents.",
          image: "https://source.unsplash.com/random/300x200/?teenagers,talking"
      }
  ],
  content: `
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-800">
          <!-- Why Early Detection Matters Section -->
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2">
              Why Early Detection Matters
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
              Recognizing the early warning signs of drug dependency can make a significant
              difference in preventing addiction from fully developing. The earlier a
              problem is identified and addressed, the better the chances for successful
              intervention and recovery. Many people who struggle with substance abuse show
              warning signs long before their use becomes a severe addiction.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
              It's important to note that these signs alone don't always indicate drug use –
              many can also be signs of other issues like depression, anxiety, or simply the
              challenges of adolescence. However, when multiple signs appear together,
              especially with sudden changes in behavior, it may be time to consider the
              possibility of substance abuse.
          </p>

          <!-- Behavioral Warning Signs Section -->
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2">
              Behavioral Warning Signs
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
              Changes in behavior are often the first noticeable signs of substance abuse.
              Be alert for these behavioral changes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-8 space-y-2">
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Sudden secretiveness</strong> - Increased privacy about activities,
                  phone use, or whereabouts
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">New friend groups</strong> - Abandoning old friends for a new social
                  circle, especially if the new group is known for drug use
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Declining performance</strong> - Decreased interest and performance
                  in work or school
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Financial issues</strong> - Unexplained need for money, missing
                  money, or selling possessions
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Legal problems</strong> - Getting into trouble with authorities,
                  such as arrests or traffic incidents
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Risk-taking behavior</strong> - Engaging in dangerous activities,
                  especially when under the influence
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Neglecting responsibilities</strong> - Failing to meet obligations
                  at home, work, or school
              </li>
          </ul>

          <!-- Expert Insight Section -->
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 my-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Expert Insight</h3>
              <p class="italic text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                  "One of the most reliable indicators is a significant shift in priorities.
                  When activities that were once important become secondary to drug use, it's
                  a strong signal that dependency may be developing."
              </p>
              <p class="text-right font-medium text-blue-800 mt-2">
                  - Dr. James Reyes, Addiction Psychiatrist
              </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Physical Warning Signs Section -->
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2">
              Physical Warning Signs
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
              Substance abuse often manifests in physical changes that might be noticed by
              family members, friends, or coworkers:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-8 space-y-2">
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Changes in appearance</strong> - Sudden weight loss or gain, neglect
                  of personal hygiene
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Sleep disturbances</strong> - Unusual sleep patterns, insomnia, or
                  excessive sleeping
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Physical symptoms</strong> - Bloodshot eyes, dilated or constricted
                  pupils, slurred speech
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Coordination issues</strong> - Impaired coordination, tremors, or
                  unsteady gait
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Health complaints</strong> - Frequent illness, nosebleeds, or
                  unexplained injuries
              </li>
              <li class="leading-relaxed">
                  <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Unusual smells</strong> - Different odors on breath, body, or
                  clothing
              </li>
          </ul>

          <!-- Conclusion Section -->
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2">
              Conclusion
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
              Early recognition of substance abuse warning signs can lead to timely
              intervention and improved outcomes. Remember that addiction is a complex
              health condition that requires compassion, understanding, and professional
              help. If you're concerned about someone you care about, approach the situation
              with empathy and focus on connecting them with appropriate resources rather
              than criticism or blame.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
              The path to recovery begins with awareness. By knowing what to look for and
              responding thoughtfully, you can be a crucial part of helping someone find
              their way back to health and well-being.
          </p>
      </div>
  `
}; %>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="text-sm breadcrumbs mb-6">
      <ul class="flex items-center text-gray-500">
          <li class="flex items-center">
              <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a>
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 mx-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center">
              <a href="/resources" class="hover:text-blue-600">Resources</a>
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 mx-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
          </li>
          <li><%= post.title %></li>
      </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
      <!-- Featured Image -->
      <div class="h-64 md:h-80 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('<%= post.featuredImage %>')"></div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="p-6 md:p-10">
          <div class="mb-8">
              <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">
                  <%= post.category %>
              </span>
              <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-blue-900 mt-4 mb-2">
                  <%= post.title %>
              </h1>
              <div class="flex items-center text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">
                  <span><%= post.date %></span>
                  <span class="mx-3">•</span>
                  <span>By <%= post.author.name %>, <%= post.author.role %></span>
              </div>
          </div>

          <%- post.content %>

          <!-- Tags -->
          <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <% post.tags.forEach(tag => { %>
                      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 rounded-full text-sm"><%= tag %></span>
                  <% }); %>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <div class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-6">Related Articles</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <% post.relatedPosts.forEach(relatedPost => { %>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition">
                  <div class="h-48 bg-cover bg-center" style="background-image: url('<%= relatedPost.image %>')"></div>
                  <div class="p-6">
                      <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-xs font-medium">
                          <%= relatedPost.category %>
                      </span>
                      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 mt-2 text-blue-900">
                          <%= relatedPost.title %>
                      </h3>
                      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 line-clamp-2">
                          <%= relatedPost.excerpt %>
                      </p>
                      <a href="/resources/<%= relatedPost.slug %>" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium inline-flex items-center">
                          Read More
                          <svg class="w-4 h-4 ml-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
                          </svg>
                      </a>
                  </div>
              </div>
          <% }); %>
      </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <div class="mt-12 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">
          Need More Information?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-6">
          We're here to help. If you have questions or need more resources about
          drug prevention, treatment, or support services, contact us or explore our
          comprehensive resource library.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/resources" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition inline-block">
              Browse Resources
          </a>
          <a href="/authorities" class="bg-white text-blue-900 hover:bg-blue-100 font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition inline-block border border-blue-200">
              Contact Support
          </a>
      </div>
  </div>
</div>